    dc:title "The oribatid mite superfamily Eutegaeoidea (Acari, Oribatida), with descriptions of new taxa from Australia and New Caledonia and a re-assessment of genera and families" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146975>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146995>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146973>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146981>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146987> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146975>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Eutegaeus woiwurrung sp. nov., immatures (a) tritonymph (Tn), dorsal aspect, bearing larval (La), protonymphal (Pn) and deutonymphal (Dn) scalps. Arrow indicates the scale associated with seta h1, but the seta itself is absent. Scale bar = 200 μm; (b) tritonymph, bothridium. Scale bar = 40 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146975/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146995>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13.Atalotegaeus crobylus sp. nov., adult (a) dorsal aspect showing notogastral setae in the centrodorsal position (cd), sub-marginal (sm) and marginal (m) positions; (b) ventral aspect. Scale bar = 200 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146995/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146973>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Eutegaeus woiwurrung sp. nov., adult (a) dorsal aspect; (b) ventral aspect; (c) detail of left notogastral seta lm. Scale bar = 200 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146973/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146981>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Eutegaeus nothofagii sp. nov. tritonymph (a) dorsal aspect with larval, protonymphal and deutonymphal scalps; (b) ventral aspect. Arrow indicates the scale associated with seta h1, but the seta itself is absent. Scale bar = 200 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146981/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146987>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Eutegaeus ptilosus sp. nov., tritonymph (a) dorsal aspect with larval, protonymphal and deutonymphal scalps; (b) ventral aspect; (c) detail of apex of seta lm. Scale bar = 200 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146987/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

